===Etymology===
[[Scottish Gaelic]] ''[[uisge]] [[beatha]]'' and [[Irish]] ''[[uisce]] [[beatha]]'' [[literally|lit.]] '[[water]] of [[life]]' (cf. [[aquavit]] < [[Latin]] ''[[aqua]] [[vitae]]'').

===Alternative spellings===
* [[whisky]]

===Noun===
'''whiskey'''

# a [[distill]]ed [[alcoholic]] [[liquor]] made from [[grain]].
# a [[drink]] of whiskey.
#The letter ''W'' in the [[ICAO spelling alphabet]].

